INDEPENDENT SERVICE AUDITOR'S REPORT
SOC 2 Type II — Acme Cloud Analytics, Inc.
Period: July 1, 2024 – December 31, 2024

SCOPE
Trust Services Criteria: Security (CC), Availability (A1)
Note: Confidentiality, Processing Integrity, and Privacy criteria are OUT OF SCOPE for this engagement.

AUDITOR OPINION
In our opinion, the description of Acme Cloud Analytics' Cloud Analytics Platform is fairly presented and
the controls were suitably designed and operating effectively throughout the period, with the exceptions
noted below.

SYSTEM DESCRIPTION
Acme Cloud Analytics provides a multi-tenant SaaS analytics platform. Customer data is stored in
AWS us-east-1 with backup to AWS us-west-2.

CONTROL EXCEPTIONS AND DEVIATIONS

CC6.1 — Logical Access Controls
EXCEPTION: During the review period, 3 of 25 sampled user accounts retained elevated administrative
privileges for 47 days after the associated employee's departure date. Root cause: manual provisioning
process lacked automated deprovisioning triggers.
MANAGEMENT RESPONSE: Vendor committed to implementing automated deprovisioning by Q2 2025.
Remediation not yet verified by auditor.

CC6.7 — Transmission of Data
EXCEPTION: Audit testing identified that 2 internal API endpoints transmit data using TLS 1.1,
which is below current minimum security standards (TLS 1.2+). Vendor acknowledged these endpoints
serve legacy customers and have not been upgraded.

CC7.2 — Monitoring of System Components
NOTE: Vendor's security information and event management (SIEM) system does not ingest logs from
third-party subprocessor environments. Coverage gap exists for incidents originating at subprocessors.

A1.2 — Environmental Protections
No exceptions noted. Vendor's primary and backup data centers demonstrated adequate environmental
controls including redundant power, HVAC, and fire suppression systems.

CC9.2 — Incident Response
EXCEPTION: During the period, one security incident (unauthorized access to a development environment)
was not escalated per Vendor's documented incident response procedure. The incident was contained
within 8 hours but was not reported to affected customers as required under the incident response policy.

ENCRYPTION AT REST
Customer data is encrypted at rest using AES-128. Note: Vendor's published policy states AES-256;
auditor confirmed that legacy storage tiers use AES-128 encryption.

PENETRATION TESTING
Annual penetration test was conducted by an internal team. No independent third-party penetration
test was performed during the audit period.

SUBPROCESSORS REVIEWED IN SCOPE
- AWS (infrastructure hosting)
- Twilio SendGrid (email notifications)
- Datadog (monitoring — partial scope only)

KEY RISK INDICATORS
- Mean time to patch critical vulnerabilities: 23 days (Vendor target: 14 days)
- Failed login attempt threshold: not configured for API authentication endpoints

Prepared by: [Audit Firm] | Report Date: February 15, 2025
